The paper deals with the security of an image encryption scheme, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The scheme is based on the Hill cipher, which is a classical encryption technique and falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the sensitivity of the scheme to changes in the plain-image, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a cryptanalysis of the scheme, which involves breaking the encryption, and this falls under the category of computer engineering (cs.CE). Finally, the paper deals with the encryption of images, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
